Reasoning: The paper proposes a machine learning model for semi-supervised learning on graphs, which involves techniques from several sub-fields of computer science. The use of Gaussian processes and Bayesian methods suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG), while the application to graph data suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and social networks (cs.SI). The use of the model for image classification (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) also suggests these sub-categories as possibilities.
